description of a financial services sales representative  credit manager  the role of a credit manager in a bank  financial services  pros  cons of a career in financial services a product manager working in the financial services industry is in charge of developing a strategy to sell a product this involves planning and assisting in the development marketing and distribution of a product product managers also have to provide a clear plan for their product outlining goals as well as potential risks challenges and opportunities they play a very active role within a company leading and motivating teams to achieve their desired outcomes educational requirements product managers who work in the financial services industry have at least a bachelor’s degree in finance marketing business management or another related field of study many individuals have a master’s degree in business administration however this position requires an extensive knowledge of finance and marketing so youll need a strong background in both fields many product managers in the financial services industry possess skills in accounting to help them balance budgets skills and experience in order to be a product manager in financial services youll need at least five years of experience in a finance or management role although most employers prefer more moreover youll need strong teamwork skills and the ability to inspire your fellow team members project managers have the necessary time and project management skills in order to complete their projects in a timely manner finally youll need to be able to use spreadsheets to analyze financial data and predict future costs revenues and profits primary responsibilities the principal duty of a product manager in financial services is to develop a strategy from inception to completion of a product youll have to work with the design and engineering teams to develop the product the marketing team to effectively market the product and outside vendors to distribute and sell your product along the way youll have to complete financial analysis to model the product’s cost and potential margin in addition youll be in charge of driving different teams and departments to make sure you achieve all of your initial goals additional duties while developing your product youll also have to present your strategy to partners and shareholders youll outline how you plan to achieve your objective and lay out the potential risks and opportunities product managers in financial services regularly meet with clients about their interests furthermore you may have to pitch your product to thirdparty vendors all of these responsibilities will require strong communication skills you may have to travel often in order to meet with customers and potential clients references  kforce financial services project managerbirch communications senior product manager about the author harlow keith has been involved in the human resources sector since  he founded a human resources training company and has written several published articles harlow became interested in his field at the tender age of  while editing his fathers resume photo credits keith brofskyphotodiscgetty images suggest an article correction related searches more articles product marketing consultant  job description for a product marketing consultant product analyst  product analyst duties banking relationship manager  job description for a commercial banking relationship manager financial reporting manager  the job description of a financial reporting manager also viewed marketing manager  how much does a marketing manager get paid product management  product management cover letter product specialist  product specialist pay scale brand champion  responsibilities  duties of a brand champion tips  tips for being a good demonstrator pay scale  pay scale for a marketing coordinator accounts receivable  the managers responsibilities for accounts receivable meet our team  meet our team our advisors jo