 of risk management products including interest rate and currency swaps caps collars commodity hedges and indexed loans enabling borrowers to manage risks occurring during the life of a given loan these hedging instruments allow borrowers to better manage the financial risks associated with their adb loans to access marketbased hedging tools using the bank as an intermediary and to actively manage their afdb debt portfolio with the introduction of guarantees in  the bank has opened up a new window of opportunity for borrowers who want to access resources from thirdparty lenders including capital markets guarantees are also an effective tool for encouraging local currency borrowing on  december  board of directors of the bank approved several amendments to the menu of the bank’s financial products these amendments include the withdrawal of the variable rate loan vlr product for all borrowers the maintenance of the temporary suspension of the fixed spread loan fsl product and the introduction of the enhanced variable spread loan evsl product for sovereign guaranteed borrowersresources latest news   afdb to invest us billion in agriculture in next  years   afdb president adesina visits ghana to strengthen cooperation   sudan afdb takes the ‘desert to power initiative’ to sudan useful linksindependent review mechanism irmintegrity and anticorruptionfinancial informationtrade finance programinitiatives  partnerships key documentsfinancial productsproject appraisal reportsprojectprogramme completion reportsloan and grant conditionsprojects performance evaluation reportcompletion report reviewsproject evaluationslending ratesrisk managementprocurement noticesintegrity  anticorruption reportsenvironmental  social assessmentsexchange rates subscribe email alerts enewsletters follow on twitter rss feeds mapafricaproject portfolioselected projectsproject cyclefinancial productsafrican development bankafrican development fundprocurementfinancial management terms  conditionsdisc